 {"id":"bd-2vr05.14.2","title":"task(links): implement OSC-8 + URL-provider hyperlink detection and annotation pipeline","description":"Background\\n- xterm.js web-links usage depends on both OSC-8 hyperlinks and plain-text URL detection/provider behavior.\\n- FrankenTermJS needs deterministic hyperlink discovery and annotation across viewport + scrollback.\\n\\nScope\\n- Preserve OSC-8 hyperlink metadata through parser/state/grid/scrollback paths.\\n- Implement deterministic URL detection/provider API with explicit ordering and conflict policy versus OSC-8.\\n- Expose hyperlink annotation data for hover, keyboard navigation, and secure activation layers.\\n\\nAcceptance\\n- Hyperlink ranges remain stable under scroll, resize, and reflow operations.\\n- Detection conflicts resolve deterministically with documented precedence.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- OSC-8 and URL-provider detection semantics are deterministic and documented (precedence, overlap, invalidation).\\n- Unit tests cover hyperlink range stability under unicode graphemes, wraps, scrollback trims, and viewport reflow.\\n- Deterministic browser E2E scripts validate hover/focus annotation correctness with structured JSONL logs.\\n- Differential checks versus xterm.js hyperlink fixtures are wired into CI for covered scenarios.\\n\\n## Mandatory Cross-Cut Quality Gate\\n- Comprehensive unit tests are required for implementation and edge-case regressions.\\n- Deterministic E2E scripts are required for impacted workflows and must run in CI.\\n- Validation output must include detailed structured logs (timestamps, correlation IDs, failure context) sufficient for deterministic replay.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- Keep link annotations in core deterministic state so selection/copy/search can consume the same canonical ranges.\\n- Explicitly log overlap-resolution decisions (OSC-8 vs provider URL) for postmortem clarity.\\n- Do not allow hyperlink metadata paths to introduce unbounded per-cell payload growth.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"FrostyGate","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-11T07:51:52.228283813Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T15:15:14.197071725Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T15:15:14.197037651Z","close_reason":"Implemented OSC-8 hyperlink propagation in terminal_engine + explicit-over-auto URL resolution in wasm link APIs/click policy; added deterministic tests and ran rch validation.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["api","frankenterm","links","parser","security","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.11.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.13.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.2","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.14.3","title":"task(image): implement bounded inline-image protocol decoding and cell-anchored rendering","description":"Background\\n- xterm.js image addon users rely on inline image protocols for modern terminal workflows.\\n- FrankenTermJS needs first-party, policy-driven support with hard resource bounds.\\n\\nScope\\n- Parse and validate selected inline image protocol envelopes (capability-gated).\\n- Implement deterministic image decode/upload pipeline with strict memory/frame budgets and eviction policy.\\n- Render cell-anchored images with correct scroll/resize/viewport behavior and fallback semantics when capabilities are unavailable.\\n\\nAcceptance\\n- Image rendering remains deterministic for fixed inputs/capability profiles.\\n- Decode/render paths enforce bounded memory and queue usage under adversarial input.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Protocol parsing/validation for supported inline-image formats is deterministic, capability-gated, and fuzz/regression tested.\\n- Unit tests cover decode limits, eviction policy, anchor semantics, and resize/scroll interactions.\\n- Deterministic browser E2E scripts validate image-heavy workloads and failure modes (oversized payloads, malformed metadata) with structured JSONL diagnostics.\\n- CI gates fail on budget regressions (memory/frame time) or semantic drift in image positioning behavior.\\n\\n## Mandatory Cross-Cut Quality Gate\\n- Comprehensive unit tests are required for implementation and edge-case regressions.\\n- Deterministic E2E scripts are required for impacted workflows and must run in CI.\\n- Validation output must include detailed structured logs (timestamps, correlation IDs, failure context) sufficient for deterministic replay.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- Keep all image protocol support explicitly capability-gated and policy-controlled by defaults.\\n- Enforce hard decode/upload caps before allocation; fail deterministically with reason-coded diagnostics.\\n- Ensure image rendering never bypasses one-writer/frame-budget invariants.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":300,"created_at":"2026-02-11T07:52:12.087634054Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T05:36:52.374427753Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T05:36:52.374343726Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["frankenterm","image","protocol","renderer","security","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.11.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.8.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.3","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.8.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.14.4","title":"task(progress): implement deterministic progress signaling API and OSC-mapped semantics","description":"Background\\n- xterm.js progress addon usage depends on exposing terminal-originated progress signals to host UI.\\n- FrankenTermJS should provide a first-party deterministic progress event surface without addon coupling.\\n\\nScope\\n- Define supported progress signal sources (including mapped escape-sequence forms) and normalization rules.\\n- Expose typed progress events with ordering guarantees and bounded delivery semantics.\\n- Integrate with host API docs and capability flags.\\n\\nAcceptance\\n- Equivalent input/replay streams produce identical progress event sequences.\\n- Unsupported/prohibited signals fail deterministically with traceable diagnostics.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Progress signal taxonomy and normalization rules are explicit, deterministic, and versioned.\\n- Unit tests cover sequence ordering, dedupe/coalescing policy, invalid signal handling, and capability gating.\\n- Browser E2E scripts validate host-visible progress lifecycle behavior with structured JSONL diagnostics.\\n- API contract tests ensure typed event payload stability and error semantics.\\n\\n## Mandatory Cross-Cut Quality Gate\\n- Comprehensive unit tests are required for implementation and edge-case regressions.\\n- Deterministic E2E scripts are required for impacted workflows and must run in CI.\\n- Validation output must include detailed structured logs (timestamps, correlation IDs, failure context) sufficient for deterministic replay.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- Keep progress events in the same deterministic ordering model as other host events.\\n- Do not leak unbounded high-frequency progress updates; enforce bounded delivery/coalescing policy.\\n- Include trace IDs linking parsed escape input to emitted host events.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"FrostyGate","estimated_minutes":150,"created_at":"2026-02-11T07:52:31.771885449Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-16T15:58:28.071293799Z","closed_at":"2026-02-16T15:58:28.071274974Z","close_reason":"Completed: OSC 9;4 terminal.progress mapping + deterministic normalization + docs/tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["api","events","frankenterm","parser","progress","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.13.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.13.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.13.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.4","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","title":"task(text-render): implement optional ligature/shaping path with deterministic fallback","description":"Background\\n- Many xterm.js users depend on ligature rendering for code readability in modern fonts.\\n- FrankenTermJS should support this as an explicit, optional capability without sacrificing deterministic core behavior.\\n\\nScope\\n- Add optional ligature/shaping render path with stable feature flags and fallback to canonical grapheme rendering.\\n- Define cache/invalidation behavior for shaped clusters and font changes.\\n- Ensure selection/cursor/extraction semantics remain correct when ligature shaping is enabled.\\n\\nAcceptance\\n- Enabling/disabling ligature mode produces predictable, documented rendering differences only.\\n- Core editing/navigation semantics remain invariant across ligature settings.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Ligature/shaping mode is capability-gated, deterministic, and documented with explicit fallback semantics.\\n- Unit tests cover shaping cache invalidation, cursor/selection boundary correctness, and copy/extract invariants under ligature mode.\\n- Browser E2E scripts validate ligature-enabled workflows across representative fonts with structured JSONL logs.\\n- Performance and memory impacts are benchmarked and gated to prevent regressions.\\n\\n## Mandatory Cross-Cut Quality Gate\\n- Comprehensive unit tests are required for implementation and edge-case regressions.\\n- Deterministic E2E scripts are required for impacted workflows and must run in CI.\\n- Validation output must include detailed structured logs (timestamps, correlation IDs, failure context) sufficient for deterministic replay.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- Treat ligatures as a rendering concern; canonical text storage and terminal semantics must remain unchanged.\\n- Document and test the exact mapping between shaped glyphs and logical cell boundaries for interaction correctness.\\n- Ensure fallback path is always available and deterministic when shaping prerequisites are missing.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-11T07:52:50.541282675Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T01:49:31.838931698Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["frankenterm","ligatures","renderer","text","unicode","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.4.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.8.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","title":"task(text-render): implement optional ligature/shaping path with deterministic fallback","description":"Background\\n- Many xterm.js users depend on ligature rendering for code readability in modern fonts.\\n- FrankenTermJS should support this as an explicit, optional capability without sacrificing deterministic core behavior.\\n\\nScope\\n- Add optional ligature/shaping render path with stable feature flags and fallback to canonical grapheme rendering.\\n- Define cache/invalidation behavior for shaped clusters and font changes.\\n- Ensure selection/cursor/extraction semantics remain correct when ligature shaping is enabled.\\n\\nAcceptance\\n- Enabling/disabling ligature mode produces predictable, documented rendering differences only.\\n- Core editing/navigation semantics remain invariant across ligature settings.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Ligature/shaping mode is capability-gated, deterministic, and documented with explicit fallback semantics.\\n- Unit tests cover shaping cache invalidation, cursor/selection boundary correctness, and copy/extract invariants under ligature mode.\\n- Browser E2E scripts validate ligature-enabled workflows across representative fonts with structured JSONL logs.\\n- Performance and memory impacts are benchmarked and gated to prevent regressions.\\n\\n## Mandatory Cross-Cut Quality Gate\\n- Comprehensive unit tests are required for implementation and edge-case regressions.\\n- Deterministic E2E scripts are required for impacted workflows and must run in CI.\\n- Validation output must include detailed structured logs (timestamps, correlation IDs, failure context) sufficient for deterministic replay.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- Treat ligatures as a rendering concern; canonical text storage and terminal semantics must remain unchanged.\\n- Document and test the exact mapping between shaped glyphs and logical cell boundaries for interaction correctness.\\n- Ensure fallback path is always available and deterministic when shaping prerequisites are missing.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-02-11T07:52:50.541282675Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T04:14:13.001780117Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["frankenterm","ligatures","renderer","text","unicode","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.4.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.6.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.8.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","title":"task(test): add addon-parity compatibility harness (unit + browser E2E + differential + structured logs)","description":"Background\\n- Addon-parity work must be validated as rigorously as core terminal behavior to avoid regressions and migration surprises.\\n\\nScope\\n- Add focused unit/property tests for fit, links, image, progress, ligature, and web-font lifecycle invariants.\\n- Add deterministic browser E2E scripts for representative workflows and adversarial cases.\\n- Add differential harness coverage versus xterm.js for scoped parity scenarios.\\n- Emit structured JSONL diagnostics with trace IDs and replay metadata.\\n\\nAcceptance\\n- CI fails on semantic drift, non-deterministic outcomes, or missing diagnostics across addon-parity tracks.\\n- Test artifacts are sufficient for deterministic replay and root-cause analysis.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Comprehensive unit tests exist for all addon-parity sub-capabilities in this feature and include edge/failure paths.\\n- Deterministic browser E2E scripts cover core workflows and adversarial scenarios for each sub-capability.\\n- Differential runs against xterm.js are integrated for scoped parity scenarios with actionable structured diff output.\\n- CI gating fails on semantic drift, non-determinism, budget regression, or missing structured diagnostics.\\n\\n## Mandatory Cross-Cut Quality Gate\\n- Comprehensive unit tests are required for implementation and edge-case regressions.\\n- Deterministic E2E scripts are required for impacted workflows and must run in CI.\\n- Validation output must include detailed structured logs (timestamps, correlation IDs, failure context) sufficient for deterministic replay.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- This bead is the enforcement gate for the entire addon-parity feature; do not mark done on partial coverage.\\n- Ensure every failure artifact includes enough context to reproduce locally without hidden state.\\n- Keep script interfaces stable so rollout/release beads can depend on canonical commands.\\n- Expected deterministic E2E script set (minimum):\\n  - tests/e2e/scripts/test_addon_fit_fonts.sh\\n  - tests/e2e/scripts/test_addon_weblinks.sh\\n  - tests/e2e/scripts/test_addon_image_protocols.sh\\n  - tests/e2e/scripts/test_addon_progress_events.sh\\n  - tests/e2e/scripts/test_addon_ligatures.sh\\n  - tests/e2e/scripts/test_addon_parity_all.sh\\n- Each script must emit JSONL traces under a canonical artifact directory and include replay seed + capability profile metadata.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-02-11T07:53:09.361336391Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-11T07:53:45.609521151Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["differential","e2e","frankenterm","logging","parity","test","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.10.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.14.6","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.14.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15","title":"epic(frankenterm-js): deterministic rescale + TeX-class real-time typography at 60+ fps","description":"North Star\\n- Eliminate remaining web rescale correctness bugs while delivering a world-class text layout engine (kerning, leading, line-break, and justification quality) that feels immediate at 60+ fps.\\n\\nFirst Principles\\n- Correctness before cleverness: layout must be deterministic for fixed inputs and capability profile.\\n- Text quality is objective-driven: spacing, breaks, and vertical rhythm are optimized with explicit cost functions, not ad-hoc heuristics.\\n- Performance is budget-governed: every frame and memory path has measurable constraints and fallback tiers.\\n- Graceful degradation is automatic: overload never causes catastrophic UX failure or semantic corruption.\\n\\nProgram Scope\\n- Web rescale hardening (ResizeObserver/DPR/zoom/font-load race windows).\\n- TeX-class paragraph layout core (incremental Knuth-Plass + hyphenation + justification).\\n- Shaping/kerning pipeline integration (cluster-safe cursor/selection/copy semantics).\\n- Adaptive quality controller under compute pressure (controller + telemetry + evidence).\\n- Exhaustive validation (unit/property/fuzz/browser E2E + structured JSONL evidence).\\n\\nOutcomes\\n- No geometry drift, stale glyph artifacts, or resize-induced interaction corruption.\\n- High-quality justified text with stable, deterministic line breaks and spacing.\\n- 60+ fps sustained on representative workloads with explicit degradation policy when budgets are violated.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Rescale correctness failures are reproducible via deterministic traces and closed by regression tests.\\n- TeX-class layout quality features (kerning/leading/justification/line-break quality) ship behind explicit capability policy with deterministic fallback.\\n- Performance budgets and degradation tiers are implemented, measured, and enforced by CI.\\n- Comprehensive unit/property/fuzz tests and browser E2E scripts exist with high-signal JSONL logs and deterministic replay metadata.\\n- Release evidence bundles prove correctness + quality + performance under normal and overload conditions.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- This epic intentionally fuses correctness, typography quality, and performance engineering into one system-level program.\\n- Existing relevant bug/parity threads to cross-reference during implementation: bd-2enu3 and bd-2vr05.14.1.\\n- Use evidence-ledger mindset: each algorithmic decision should expose rationale and measurable impact.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":7200,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:38.215451002Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:38.667176306Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["degradation","frankenterm","layout","performance","typography","wasm","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","title":"feature(web-rescale): deterministic geometry/reflow pipeline and bug eradication","description":"Goal\\n- Remove remaining web rescale/reflow bugs by making geometry transitions deterministic across container resize, DPR shifts, zoom, orientation, and font-load races.\\n\\nWhy\\n- Current bug reports and prior notes indicate multi-signal resize interactions can still produce transient corruption or drift under real browser conditions.\\n\\nScope\\n- Deterministic event ordering/coalescing across ResizeObserver, visualViewport, orientation, and explicit zoom updates.\\n- Geometry invariant enforcement from Rust/WASM core through canvas CSS/backbuffer sync.\\n- Patch baseline/reset semantics across size transitions to prevent stale diff artifacts.\\n- Regression harnesses for resize storms and pathological interleavings.","acceptance_criteria":"## Acceptance Criteria\\n- Equivalent resize/DPR/zoom/font-load traces produce identical geometry + cursor/selection outcomes.\\n- No stale-diff artifacts, garbled cells, or input-coordinate corruption under resize storms.\\n- Unit + browser E2E tests cover ordering races and pathological sequences with structured JSONL diagnostics.\\n- CI regression gates fail on geometry drift, frame hash mismatches, or missing trace evidence.","notes":"Execution Notes\\n- Keep host JS thin; source-of-truth geometry and invariants remain in Rust/WASM.\\n- Explicitly track and document tie-break rounding policies to avoid cross-browser divergence.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","estimated_minutes":960,"created_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:39.100971273Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T01:40:39.561849107Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dpr","fit","geometry","resize","wasm","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-2vr05.15.1","depends_on_id":"bd-2vr05.15","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:26:00Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
