 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.10","title":"epic(opentui-import): Alien-graveyard uplift for synthesis, formal assurance, and shadow-run adoption","description":"Background:\nThis epic operationalizes alien-graveyard + alien-artifact-coding methods so OpenTUI→FrankenTUI migration is not heuristic glue code, but a formally constrained, executable, replayable decision system with strong safety/fallback behavior.\n\nNorth star:\nConvert advanced math and systems ideas into production-grade, deterministic migration policy that improves outcomes while remaining auditable and operator-safe.\n\nCapability pillars:\n1) Contracts + provenance:\n- Contracts-as-code engine, artifact-graph IDs, claim/evidence/policy/trace linkage.\n2) Formal decision core:\n- Closed-form Bayesian posterior + expected-loss policy + formal guarantee wrappers.\n3) Graveyard executable workflow:\n- Symptom-router/Fast-Start harvesting, composability/risk matrices, entry-header/graduation schema, graveyardctl verification.\n4) Robust artifact-coding extensions:\n- Dependence-aware conjugate fusion, sequential FDR wealth control, minimal-flip counterfactual audits, graceful degradation compiler, assumption applicability checker, L0-L3 galaxy-brain contracts.\n5) Testing and proof gates:\n- Deep unit/property suites + end-to-end gauntlets with deterministic replay artifacts and red-path safety diagnostics.\n6) Release enforcement:\n- RC promotion blocked unless all mandatory alien + optimization + certification gauntlets pass and artifact clauses are machine-valid.\n\nExecution map (high level):\n- Foundation + governance track: .10.1-.10.20\n- Formal inference/guarantee track: .10.21-.10.28\n- Graveyard executable track: .10.29-.10.37\n- Advanced artifact-coding track: .10.38-.10.45\n\nSuccess criteria:\n1) Every advanced primitive/controller has budgeted mode, deterministic fallback, and replayable evidence traces.\n2) Recommendation contracts are machine-linted for EV/tier, metadata schema, risk countermeasures, guarantees, comparator, rollback, and demo linkage completeness.\n3) Mandatory gauntlets pass for route→rank→contract→verify→demo→release pipelines before RC promotion.\n4) CI fails on missing artifacts, unsafe composition, violated assumptions, invalid guarantees, or policy-breaking optimizations.\n5) Operators can reconstruct any migration decision (and nearest counterfactual flip) from structured logs alone.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:49:38.728311183Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T22:46:25.850012731Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["alien-graveyard","formal-methods","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.10","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:49:38.728311183Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
